# Technology Stack: Open-Source & Licensing Guidance

This document confirms that all recommended technologies in your architecture are **free and open-source** (or have generous free tiers) and can be used without restriction for this nonprofit volunteer project.

---

## Frontend Technologies

### React (or Vue)
- **License**: MIT License (permissive open-source)
- **Freedom to Use**: ✅ **Completely free** for any project, including commercial and nonprofit
- **Cost**: $0
- **Notes**: MIT is one of the most permissive licenses; no restrictions on how you use it
- **Alternative**: Vue.js (also MIT licensed, slightly lighter weight)

### TypeScript
- **License**: Apache 2.0 License (permissive open-source)
- **Freedom to Use**: ✅ **Completely free**
- **Cost**: $0
- **Notes**: Built-in support for better code quality and developer experience

### Material-UI or Bootstrap (optional UI framework)
- **License**: MIT License
- **Freedom to Use**: ✅ **Completely free**
- **Cost**: $0

---

## Backend Technologies

### FastAPI (Python)
- **License**: MIT License
- **Freedom to Use**: ✅ **Completely free**
- **Cost**: $0
- **Notes**: Modern, fast, great for building APIs quickly. Ideal for integrating LLMs and AI agents
- **Python itself**: PSF License (fully open-source, free)

### Node.js / Express (alternative)
- **License**: MIT License (Node.js) / MIT License (Express)
- **Freedom to Use**: ✅ **Completely free**
- **Cost**: $0
- **Notes**: If you prefer JavaScript across frontend and backend

---

## Database Technologies

### PostgreSQL
- **License**: PostgreSQL License (very permissive open-source)
- **Freedom to Use**: ✅ **Completely free**, even for commercial use
- **Cost**: $0 (self-hosted) or ~$15–50/month on cloud (e.g., Heroku, Railway, Supabase)
- **Notes**: Enterprise-grade, no licensing restrictions, widely used by nonprofits

### SQLite (alternative for local development)
- **License**: Public Domain
- **Freedom to Use**: ✅ **Completely free**
- **Cost**: $0
- **Notes**: Perfect for early prototyping, no database server needed

---

## Vector Database / Embeddings

### Chroma
- **License**: Apache 2.0 License
- **Freedom to Use**: ✅ **Completely free**
- **Cost**: $0 (self-hosted) or free tier on cloud
- **Notes**: Open-source vector database, perfect for storing and querying embeddings for matching

### Pinecone (alternative)
- **License**: Proprietary (but free tier available)
- **Freedom to Use**: ✅ **Free tier includes 125K vectors**, more than enough for prototype
- **Cost**: $0 (free tier) or ~$12/month for production tier
- **Notes**: Managed service (easier setup than self-hosting), generous free tier

### FAISS (Meta/Facebook's Vector Search)
- **License**: MIT License
- **Freedom to Use**: ✅ **Completely free**
- **Cost**: $0
- **Notes**: Alternative to Chroma; slightly more complex setup but highly performant

---

